lenders.loan_because: In all seriousness.... Allmost everyone needs assistance in life. My parents have help me a bunch and this is something I can do with my relative small resources. I've been making loans for several years and have an 87% payback rate. My payback rate is lower than most due to a single larger amount that was not paid back but honestly.... I don't care.... If anything I worry more about the one who could not pay back rather than any regret. I wish that I could follow up with this individual....I'd rather give more and ensure she does not feel bad. I've only made a couple tiny donations on the zip network with some remaining money but plan to add more soon especially since the interest charged to borrowers is much less than the traditional kiva.com
lenders.occupational_info: Give this gift to others....when my loans are paid back I send the $ and info to a friend and explain how I loaned $250.... Or whatever the number was and all of it was paid back. I then let them choose how to pass it on. I never follow up with people....some have never passed the $ on (I got a notice that it was being donated due to lack of activity) but most have donated and added to the fund since they tell me about it.

lenders.name: Frankie
lenders.loan_because:
In the summer and fall of 2010, I had the distinct fortune to live in Buenos Aires, Argentina and to visit other South American countries (including Peru and Uruguay). In Buenos Aires, I studied Argentine literature, philosophy and art. More importantly, I studied life and people. I feel very lucky to have experienced what I experienced there, and to have learned the timeless lessons that these experiences offered. I loan because-as long as I have the means to help others-I feel it is my duty as a human to do so. I wish happiness and success to all of the lenders and borrowers. 
Peace, Frankie
---------------------------------
Durante el verano y otoño de 2010, yo tuve la suerte de vivir en Buenos Aires, Argentina y de visitar otros países en Suramérica (incluyendo Peru y Uruguay). En Buenos Aires, estudiaba la literatura Argentina, la filosofía y el arte. Lo que es más importante es que estudiaba la vida y la gente. Siento re suerte que he experimentado lo que experimentaba allí y que he aprendido todas las lecciones eternas que esas experiencias proveyeron. Presto porque-mientras puedo ayudar otras personas-siento que es mi obligación hacerlo. Deseo la felicidad y el éxito a todos los prestamistas y los prestatarios. 
Paz, Frankie
